Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.19,0:00:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, and welcome to this month’s broadcast! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.92,0:00:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,With me I have a good friend \Nas my cohost, Leon Weaver. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.19,0:00:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Leon, what do we have \Nto look forward to this time?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.30,0:00:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Brother Lösch. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.03,0:00:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll see a young brother who must choose \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.57,0:00:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,between his loyalty to Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.57,0:00:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,or to a close friend. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.57,0:00:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Which will he choose? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.78,0:00:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we’ll hear the story of Rafika Morris, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.98,0:00:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,a young woman \Nwho desperately fought for racial equality \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.38,0:00:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but eventually discovers \Nthe real path to peace. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.66,0:00:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’ll also enjoy a new music video \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.76,0:00:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that beautifully highlights the importance \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.59,0:00:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of putting our confidence in Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.36,0:00:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We have much to look forward to \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.97,0:00:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in this March 2018 edition \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.50,0:00:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of JW Broadcasting! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.86,0:01:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The theme for this month is\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.06,0:01:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“In Whom Do You Trust?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.06,0:01:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you trust me? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.20,0:01:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope so. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.43,0:01:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,All of us want to be trusted. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.43,0:01:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust is a basic element of everyday life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.67,0:01:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,To trust others is a normal reaction. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.74,0:01:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of us have traveled on a train or a bus. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.24,0:01:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Did we worry whether \Nthe conductor or driver \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.11,0:01:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,would bring us safely to our destination? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.72,0:01:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Normally, we do not worry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.29,0:01:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We trust an airplane captain \Nto take us safely to our destination. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.62,0:01:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We trust that when we enter an elevator, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.83,0:01:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it will not crash at the bottom of the shaft,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.60,0:01:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,but safely take us to the desired floor. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.37,0:02:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,When we marry, we trust that \Nour partner will remain faithful. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.90,0:02:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In many situations in life we need trust. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.07,0:02:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What is trust? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.78,0:02:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust is the “firm belief in the reliability,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.45,0:02:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,truth, or ability of someone or something.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.08,0:02:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Webster’s dictionary says \Nthat it is “confidence”; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.52,0:02:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,a “reliance [or] resting \Nof the mind on the integrity, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.56,0:02:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“veracity, justice, friendship, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.56,0:02:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,or other sound principle, of another person.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.97,0:02:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust is related to confidence, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.50,0:02:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,belief, faith, and assurance. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.81,0:02:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Experiments conducted \Nby Professor Dr. Michael Kosfeld,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.74,0:02:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,a professor at a university \Nin Frankfurt, Germany,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.32,0:02:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,led him to the conclusion that trust \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.82,0:02:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is “a biologically-based part \Nof human nature.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.39,0:02:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Kosfeld discovered that when \Nthere is interaction between two people, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.39,0:03:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the human brain releases \Na hormone that stimulates trust. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.77,0:03:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“It is, in fact, \None of the distinguishing features \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.67,0:03:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of the human species,” Kosfeld states.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.18,0:03:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,In everyday life, how discouraged \Nsome are if they are not trusted. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.05,0:03:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The phrase “Don’t you trust me?”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.98,0:03:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is frequently heard with an undertone\Nof sadness or complaint. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.72,0:03:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes children or teenagers\Nask their parents\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.86,0:03:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“Don’t you trust me?” when the parents\Nplace some restrictions on them,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.23,0:03:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps in connection\Nwith leisure-time activities. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.57,0:03:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Parents do that because they\Nlove you young ones\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.04,0:03:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and want to prevent any spiritual\Nor physical harm befalling you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.07,0:03:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If you cooperate, you will see that parents \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.64,0:03:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,will gradually trust you ever more\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.08,0:03:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and grant more liberty to you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.98,0:03:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You can prove to them\Nthat you are trustworthy.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.22,0:04:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,In the world, \Nmany people are not trustworthy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.02,0:04:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Since we are living in the time of the end\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.93,0:04:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and the demons are desperate \Nand have influenced many people,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.16,0:04:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to admit that\Ntrusting in everybody is not wise. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.50,0:04:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Many trusted in religion\Nand were disappointed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.14,0:04:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Others trusted in governments\Nor the United Nations,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.81,0:04:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,but they were disappointed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.81,0:04:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They trusted political leaders\Nthat made all kinds of promises\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.38,0:04:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but did not keep all of them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.62,0:04:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Some politicians were\Neven exposed as being liars. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.89,0:04:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 14:15 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.33,0:04:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“The naive person believes every word,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.16,0:04:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,but the shrewd one ponders each step.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.73,0:04:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If somebody, even in the truth,\Npromises us big monetary returns\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.50,0:04:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,if we give him money\Nfor his planned investment,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.31,0:04:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,we need to be careful\Nand not believe every word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.78,0:04:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Some that spent their money\Nwere in for a disappointment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.32,0:05:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when they learned that everything was lost. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.49,0:05:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We also should not trust everything we read\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.02,0:05:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in newspapers or see on television.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.49,0:05:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There is another thing\Nwe should not trust in—riches. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.43,0:05:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Psalm 49:6 speaks\Nabout “those who are trusting in their wealth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.17,0:05:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and who boast about their great riches.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.44,0:05:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Trusting in riches\Noften leads to disappointment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.41,0:05:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“The one trusting in his riches will fall,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.51,0:05:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,says Proverbs 11:28. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.32,0:05:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not wrong to be rich; \Njust do not trust in riches. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.29,0:05:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Riches are a risk factor. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.16,0:05:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Many people today are dishonest and cheat. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.16,0:05:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Some business owners have installed\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.46,0:05:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,cameras at the workplace,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.60,0:05:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,since they do not trust their employees\Nto put in a full day of work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.30,0:05:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They know that some would play\Nvideo games during work hours.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.41,0:06:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah created us\Nwith the inclination to trust. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.11,0:06:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We can especially trust\Nour spiritual brothers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.65,0:06:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,True, once in a while\Nsuch trust is misplaced. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.52,0:06:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,A few commit serious sins\Nand have to be disfellowshipped. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.79,0:06:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But that is rare. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.93,0:06:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah himself is\Nthe best example of trusting in others. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.77,0:06:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He trusted the Logos to faithfully cooperate\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.80,0:06:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,with him as the “master worker”\Nin creating the universe, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.01,0:06:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the earth, and all the living things\Non earth, including mankind. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.38,0:06:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What tremendous trust Jehovah showed\Nin Jesus when He sent him to the earth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.39,0:06:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah trusted that\NJesus would remain faithful\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.22,0:06:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and redeem mankind \Nso that His will and purpose with mankind\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.06,0:06:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and the earth could be accomplished. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.66,0:06:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah trusted him so much\Nthat he arranged for prophecies\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.10,0:07:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to be written that foretold\Nthat he would die faithfully. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.84,0:07:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This trust on the part of Jehovah\Nwas not a risk. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.81,0:07:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It was based on the collaboration\Nbetween the two for aeons of time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.32,0:07:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of the prophecy at Psalm 16:10: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.62,0:07:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“For you will not leave me in the Grave.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.39,0:07:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus had free will. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.39,0:07:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This means that theoretically \Nhe could have sinned. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.83,0:07:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If he could not have sinned, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.10,0:07:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan probably would not have tried\Nthree times to tempt Jesus to sin. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.14,0:07:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If Jesus could not have sinned, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.17,0:07:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,why would he be so heavily distressed\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.28,0:07:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in the garden of Gethsemane\Nthat he was sweating blood? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.61,0:07:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Why send an angel\Nto comfort and strengthen him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.82,0:07:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,if he could not sin or fail anyway? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.32,0:07:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No question that Jesus\Nfelt the unfathomable load\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.86,0:07:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,on his shoulders to remain faithful, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.06,0:08:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,since not only the salvation\Nof mankind depended on him\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.13,0:08:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but also the vindication\Nof Jehovah’s sovereignty. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.27,0:08:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He did not want to disappoint Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.17,0:08:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus used his own free will\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.21,0:08:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and was determined to stay loyal. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.45,0:08:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,How glad we are that he did!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.95,0:08:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, \NJesus also trusted Jehovah completely. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.09,0:08:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He trusted Jehovah that he would\Nresurrect him if he would die faithfully. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.19,0:08:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, Jesus was publicly known\Nto trust in Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.46,0:08:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,People that passed by when he was\Non the torture stake were saying:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.44,0:08:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“He has put his trust in God;\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.14,0:08:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“let Him now rescue him if He wants him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.88,0:08:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,for he said, ‘I am God’s Son.’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.28,0:08:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Another example of trust was Abraham. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.45,0:08:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When God told him\Nto kill his beloved son Isaac, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.92,0:08:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Abraham was willing to do so. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.39,0:09:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He trusted that Jehovah could resurrect him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.09,0:09:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hebrews 11:19 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.36,0:09:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“He reasoned that God was able to raise\Nhim up even from the dead, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.13,0:09:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and he did receive him from there\Nin an illustrative way.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.74,0:09:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,First Corinthians 13:7 says that\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.67,0:09:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,love “believes all things.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.68,0:09:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Love trusts that prophecies will come true. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.98,0:09:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It also believes what our brothers tell us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.95,0:09:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It also helps to grant others\Nthe benefit of the doubt\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.85,0:09:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,if a matter could be interpreted\Nin different ways. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.26,0:09:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, trusting others\Nis an expression of love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.46,0:09:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you love somebody, you only assume\Nand think the best of him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.57,0:09:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Another example of trust\Nin Jehovah was Moses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.54,0:09:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He led the nation of Israel\Nout of Egypt into the desert\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.01,0:09:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,—a nation upwards of three million people. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.61,0:10:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And they had flocks\Nof cattle and sheep with them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.02,0:10:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,When he left Egypt, \Ndid he know how to provide\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.02,0:10:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,these great crowds with water in the desert? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.09,0:10:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he know what they would be eating\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.53,0:10:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,after the initial foodstuffs\Nthat they took out of Egypt ran out? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.50,0:10:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he know in advance that Jehovah \Nwould miraculously provide the manna? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.94,0:10:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn’t seem so. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.97,0:10:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But he trusted that Jehovah \Nwould take care of the people.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.05,0:10:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The three friends of Daniel\Nwere another fine example of trust. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.18,0:10:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They did not bow and worship\Nin front of an idol\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.85,0:10:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that King Nebuchadnezzar had set up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.22,0:10:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They were told they would be thrown\Ninto a fiery furnace if they disobeyed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.23,0:10:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They remained firm\Nand were protected by an angel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.63,0:10:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the fire did not do any harm to them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.70,0:10:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,After that\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.37,0:10:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“Nebuchadnezzar then declared: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.04,0:11:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Praised be the God of Shadrach, \NMeshach, and Abednego, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.51,0:11:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘who sent his angel\Nand rescued his servants. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.82,0:11:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘They trusted in him and went against\Nthe command of the king\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.05,0:11:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and were willing to die rather than serve\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.29,0:11:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,or worship any god except their own God.’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.63,0:11:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,As we are getting ever closer\Nto the great tribulation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.13,0:11:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we might be confronted with scary challenges\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.27,0:11:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and tests related to nationalism. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.67,0:11:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Will we keep trusting Jehovah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.44,0:11:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We trust we will. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.48,0:11:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will miraculously save his \Npeople throughout the great tribulation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.21,0:11:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and arrange for their survival.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.95,0:11:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, the faithful slave is put in charge\Nof providing spiritual food for God’s people, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.96,0:11:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who number into the millions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.06,0:11:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The slave also shows\Ncomplete trust in Jehovah\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.50,0:11:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that he will guide them with his holy spirit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.47,0:11:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What makes it possible \Nfor the “faithful and discreet slave” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.70,0:12:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to provide precious spiritual food? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.67,0:12:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will give you insight and instruct you\Nin the way you should go,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.48,0:12:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,says Jehovah at Psalm 32:8. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.48,0:12:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, Jehovah provides direction\Nto the slave through Jesus. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.82,0:12:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus, in turn, \Nprovides direction for his people\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.26,0:12:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,through “the faithful and discreet slave.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.16,0:12:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We can therefore have full confidence\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.76,0:12:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Scriptural insight, \Nunderstanding, and guidance.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.84,0:12:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan tries to sow mistrust. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.44,0:12:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Under Communist dictatorship in Romania,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.28,0:12:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,secret police officers\Nforced a responsible brother\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.48,0:12:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to walk with them\Non a heavily frequented street\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.61,0:12:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,hoping that other brothers would see this \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.25,0:12:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and wrongly conclude that this brother\Nworks with the secret police. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.22,0:12:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Did the scheme work out? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.22,0:12:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it failed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.53,0:13:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers did see him but kept trusting him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.83,0:13:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We learn that we should not quickly\Nlose trust in our brothers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.17,0:13:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan also has the scheme \Nto spread rumors about faithful brothers,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.98,0:13:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,including the faithful slave. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.25,0:13:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The method of spreading rumors is not new. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.45,0:13:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,When Jesus was resurrected\Nand the tomb was empty, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.79,0:13:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the soldiers who reported it \Nwere told to spread the rumor\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.29,0:13:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that the disciples came \Nand stole the body at night. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.89,0:13:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Matthew 28:15 relates:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.63,0:13:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“So they took the silver pieces\Nand did as they were instructed, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.94,0:13:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and this story has been spread abroad\Namong the Jews up to this very day.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.88,0:13:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Another rumor in the first century\Nwas that Christians\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.74,0:13:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,were responsible for the great fire of Rome. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.05,0:13:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Could such an accusation be true? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.58,0:13:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Historians say that it was Nero, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.69,0:14:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the emperor, who set fire to the city.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.43,0:14:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, rumors are occasionally being spread\Nin electronic form about the faithful slave. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.43,0:14:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This has caused some concern\Non the part of some brothers,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.97,0:14:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,especially when the reports\Nare commenting on court cases\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.17,0:14:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,where some in the organization were accused. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.14,0:14:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes reference is made to certain quotes\Nand then readers think, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.08,0:14:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,‘How can a quote be a rumor?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.55,0:14:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,A quote can be taken out of context. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.05,0:14:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Critical reports often \Ngive only part of a matter\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.39,0:14:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and leave out other aspects. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.43,0:14:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Often, such rumors play on the emotions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.67,0:14:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask yourself: ‘Am I prone to believe rumors? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.67,0:14:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,‘And even if I am, should I spread it\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.31,0:14:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,‘and undermine the trust\Nthat others have in the slave \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.34,0:14:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,or in representatives of the branch office?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.85,0:15:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Avoid sensationalism \Nby not saying something like\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.09,0:15:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“Can you believe what I heard\Nabout this matter or that matter\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.92,0:15:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,or this person or that person?” \Nreferring to a statement \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.33,0:15:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that may have appeared\Non Facebook, YouTube, or Twitter. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.33,0:15:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The spread of rumors is like wildfire\Nthat is hard to control. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.34,0:15:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It spreads distrust\Nand can undermine someone’s faith. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.91,0:15:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not to say that the slave is perfect\Nand never makes mistakes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.51,0:15:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah and Jesus\Ntrust the imperfect slave \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.35,0:15:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,who cares for things\Nto the best of his ability\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.19,0:15:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and with the best of motives. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.62,0:15:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn’t we then trust\Nthe imperfect slave as well?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.86,0:15:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,To appreciate the extent of Jehovah\Nand Jesus’ trust in the faithful slave,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.87,0:15:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,reflect on what he has promised its members. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.60,0:16:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He has promised them\Nimmortality and incorruption. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.18,0:16:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon, just before Armageddon,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.58,0:16:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the remaining members of the slave\Nwill be taken to heaven. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.85,0:16:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Since 1919 of our Common Era,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.32,0:16:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the slave has been put in charge\Nof some belongings of Christ. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.96,0:16:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,According to Matthew 24:47, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.36,0:16:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,when the anointed are taken to heaven,\NJesus will at that point entrust\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.30,0:16:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“all his belongings” to them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.17,0:16:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Does this not reveal immense trust? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.41,0:16:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Revelation 4:4 describes \Nthese resurrected anointed\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.81,0:16:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,as corulers with Christ. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.42,0:16:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Revelation 22:5 says they will rule,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.42,0:16:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,not only for a thousand years\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.65,0:16:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but “forever and ever.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.13,0:16:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What immense trust \NJesus shows toward them! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.63,0:16:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Since Jehovah God and Jesus Christ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.00,0:17:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,completely trust\N“the faithful and discreet slave,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.47,0:17:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,should we not do the same?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.24,0:17:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Many servants of Jehovah in the past \Nshowed trust in Jehovah\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.78,0:17:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,when confronted with obstacles or opposition. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.58,0:17:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We can trust that Jehovah will not let us\Nbe tested beyond what we can bear\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.59,0:17:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but will provide a “way out” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.12,0:17:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,so we can remain faithful under trials. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.63,0:17:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So whom do you trust? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.80,0:17:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You fully trust in Jehovah, \NJesus, and the faithful slave. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.60,0:17:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,To a reasonable degree, you also trust all\Nyour fellow brothers and sisters.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.31,0:17:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The writer of Psalm 119:42\Nmentioned something else we need to trust in\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.31,0:17:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,—God’s Word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.32,0:17:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He wrote: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.35,0:17:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“For I put my trust in your word.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.36,0:17:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The prophecies in God’s Word\Nhave always come true at the proper time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.36,0:18:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Based on that, we can fully trust that\Nthe remaining prophecies\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.93,0:18:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,pointing to the survival\Nof the great tribulation\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.40,0:18:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and to the Paradise to follow\Nwill also come true, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.31,0:18:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,without the slightest possibility of failure.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.94,0:18:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we should trust\Nnot only Jehovah, Jesus,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.15,0:18:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the faithful slave, and the Bible \Nbut also our fellow brothers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.15,0:18:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostle Paul is a fine example of this. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.26,0:18:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He wrote to Philemon \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.76,0:18:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,asking him to kindly receive back \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.06,0:18:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the runaway slave Onesimus\Nwho had become a brother. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.07,0:18:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul wrote at Philemon 21: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.24,0:18:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am confident that you will comply,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.21,0:18:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,so I am writing you, knowing that you\Nwill do even more than what I say.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.38,0:18:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,When we speak of trust, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.45,0:18:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,we sometimes think of a little child\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.12,0:18:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,walking hand in hand with his father. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.62,0:19:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The child does not question\Nwhere the father will take him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.29,0:19:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The child trusts the father. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.99,0:19:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All throughout the last days, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.10,0:19:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,true Christians have faced hostility \Nof so many in the world. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.10,0:19:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How strengthening Jehovah’s promise is\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.84,0:19:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in view of the impending attack\Nby Satan’s hordes! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.64,0:19:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,When they attack, Jehovah’s people\Nwill seem as defenseless. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.55,0:19:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But we do not need to quake with fear. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.05,0:19:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We trust that Jehovah, Jesus, and the angels\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.32,0:19:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,will fight to deliver us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.99,0:19:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We will not shrink back in fear. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.06,0:19:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,At Hebrews 10:39, Paul wrote:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.93,0:19:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“Now we are not the sort \Nwho shrink back to destruction,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.27,0:19:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,but the sort who have faith\Nfor the preserving of our lives.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.87,0:19:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Today and after Armageddon, all can say,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.64,0:19:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,according to Psalm 26:1 and 52:8: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.94,0:19:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“I have trusted [in Jehovah]\Nwithout wavering.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.21,0:20:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“My trust is in God’s loyal love,\Nforever and ever.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.05,0:20:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, keep trusting in Jehovah \Nand those who are proving loyal to him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.06,0:20:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Back to you, Leon.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.96,0:20:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Brother Lösch. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.13,0:20:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In line with that, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.36,0:20:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,we all want \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.37,0:20:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,good friends \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.37,0:20:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,we can trust\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.13,0:20:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,—the type \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.80,0:20:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,mentioned at Proverbs 18:24, \Nwhere it says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.01,0:20:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“There is a friend \Nwho sticks closer than a brother.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.64,0:20:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But at times, \Nwe may find that a close friend \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.48,0:20:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,needs spiritual help. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.65,0:20:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we fear losing \Nthat friendship if we speak up? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.19,0:20:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What does Jehovah want us to do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.32,0:20:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following dramatization, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.03,0:20:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the young man Danny \Nfaces these same questions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.41,0:21:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a secret. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.42,0:21:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Only it wasn’t mine to tell. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.32,0:21:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It was my best friend’s, Julian.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.20,0:21:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This was not the Julian I knew.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.32,0:21:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of the meeting, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.52,0:21:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Max wanted to know \Nif I was OK. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.73,0:21:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I shrugged it off. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.73,0:21:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I just didn’t know \Nwho to talk to at that point.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.38,0:22:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,A few years ago, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.75,0:22:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when my parents \Nstopped attending meetings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.19,0:22:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Julian was there for me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.98,0:22:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t want to lose my friend. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.92,0:22:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But did I really know him?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.97,0:23:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided to ask Julian \Nabout the pictures he posted.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.71,0:23:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I told him it wasn’t right. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.88,0:23:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He needed to talk to the elders. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.41,0:23:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he got really defensive about it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.62,0:23:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew I did the right thing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.69,0:23:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,When was I supposed \Nto take care of this bill? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.06,0:23:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve been telling you \Nfor the past month! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.06,0:23:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I just needed someone to talk to. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.83,0:23:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When did you tell me? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.00,0:23:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve been working \Nfor the past couple of weeks. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.50,0:23:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, as if I don’t work? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.50,0:23:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Now you’re going \Nto blame everything on me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.45,0:23:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Max wanted to know \Nhow I was really doing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.82,0:23:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He could tell something was wrong. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.89,0:24:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So I opened up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.03,0:24:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I told him everything. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.10,0:24:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t want to get my friend in trouble. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.14,0:24:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Max understood. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.71,0:24:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He asked me to read James 5:14, 15: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.82,0:24:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“Is there anyone sick among you? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.32,0:24:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“Let him call \Nthe elders of the congregation to him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.46,0:24:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“and let them pray over him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.29,0:24:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“applying oil to him \Nin the name of Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.03,0:24:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“And the prayer of faith \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.60,0:24:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“will make the sick one well, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.27,0:24:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jehovah will raise him up.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.24,0:24:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Max showed me that the elders \Ncan encourage and strengthen \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.88,0:25:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,a spiritually weak person. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.19,0:25:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Covering up a friend’s wrongdoing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.25,0:25:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,prevents him from getting \Nthe spiritual help he needs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.76,0:25:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,All this time, \NI was focused on Julian and his deception, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.66,0:25:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and I didn’t speak up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.44,0:25:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m glad I was honest with Brother Max. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.24,0:25:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The elders are like our spiritual doctors, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.51,0:25:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and even more, they’re our friends. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.51,0:25:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They want to help us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.85,0:25:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Julian might receive discipline, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.68,0:25:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,but that’s an expression of Jehovah’s love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.19,0:25:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It could save his spiritual life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.53,0:25:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Julian got the spiritual help he needed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.07,0:26:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And I kept my best friend. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.32,0:26:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice how our young brother \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.16,0:26:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,put trust in the Bible and acted accordingly? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.73,0:26:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we do the same? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.63,0:26:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Ron Curzan’s morning worship \Ncomments share some thoughts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.67,0:26:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,on specific ways we can continue \Nto make spiritual adjustments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.24,0:26:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,as we encounter \Na variety of life’s challenges.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.72,0:26:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,These were very practical comments. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.45,0:26:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And they all tie in well \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.99,0:26:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,with what the apostle Paul was trying to tell \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.72,0:26:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,those in the Ephesian congregation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.76,0:26:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,about examining themselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.83,0:26:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The same way we have to do today \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.83,0:26:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,—examining ourselves \Nso that we please Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.63,0:26:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’d like, \Nplease open up to Ephesians chapter 5, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.70,0:27:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ll read verse 10, \Nwhich is our theme scripture. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.41,0:27:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Ephesians 5:10, it says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.28,0:27:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“Keep on making sure \Nof what is acceptable to the Lord.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.68,0:27:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it goes on in verse 11: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.68,0:27:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“And stop sharing in the unfruitful works \Nthat belong to the darkness; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.69,0:27:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,rather, expose them for what they are.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.49,0:27:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So it’s very clear to us, \Nin this chapter of Ephesians chapter 5, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.50,0:27:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that there are things \Nthat Jehovah views as acceptable \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.07,0:27:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and things he views as unacceptable. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.10,0:27:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s standard of what is unacceptable \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.11,0:27:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is outlined in quite a few \Nof the verses in chapter 5 here. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.64,0:27:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you would just scan \Nthrough verses 3, 4, and 5, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.48,0:27:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll see that unwholesome talk about sex, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.58,0:27:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,shameful conduct, obscene jesting \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.95,0:27:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,—and then verse 18, drunkenness—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.79,0:28:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,well, these are things \Nthat will bar us from God’s Kingdom. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.60,0:28:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,When you think \Nabout entertainment today, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.70,0:28:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s nearly impossible \Nto try to find something \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.20,0:28:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that is acceptable to Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.50,0:28:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that does not have \Nimmoral sex, pornography, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.74,0:28:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritism, and violence. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.17,0:28:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan has thoroughly saturated \Nall forms of the media. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.41,0:28:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So thoroughly, \Nthat it’s in our literature, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.78,0:28:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s in movies, \Nit’s in electronic games, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.12,0:28:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and everything that we \Ncan think of Satan has infiltrated. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.29,0:28:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he knows that Jehovah \Nhates these things, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.86,0:28:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and he doesn’t mind if part of our heart \Nhates these things \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.00,0:28:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,as long as part of our heart \Nloves these things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.67,0:28:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So we do well to ask ourselves: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.97,0:28:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Does the entertainment that I choose help me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.71,0:28:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,‘in my being acceptable to Jehovah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.54,0:28:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Does it help me to have the qualities \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.74,0:28:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,‘that Jehovah endears in me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.85,0:28:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and will he draw closer to me?’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.05,0:28:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the spirit of the world \Nreflects rebellion of the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.19,0:29:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,which outlines \NJehovah’s qualities and his standards. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.26,0:29:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to show respect for the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.73,0:29:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,which teaches us \Nto love what Jehovah loves \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.93,0:29:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and hate what he hates. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.77,0:29:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And what will help us to do this \Nand resist the spirit of the world \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.87,0:29:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and draw closer to Jehovah \Nand be acceptable to him? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.97,0:29:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s notice verse 17, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.97,0:29:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,chapter 5 and verse 17, it says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.18,0:29:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“On this account stop being unreasonable, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.65,0:29:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but keep perceiving \Nwhat the will of Jehovah is.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.62,0:29:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to constantly think: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.62,0:29:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,‘What would Jehovah want me to do?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.09,0:29:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, verse 1 and verse 2 \Nhelp us to appreciate this, it says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.99,0:29:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“Become imitators of God, \Nas beloved children, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.96,0:29:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“and go on walking in love, \Njust as the Christ also loved us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.17,0:29:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“and [he] gave himself [up] \Nfor us as an offering \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.07,0:29:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and a sacrifice, \Na sweet fragrance to God.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.14,0:29:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So, bottom line, \Nwe need to imitate Jehovah and Jesus. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.45,0:30:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Our sacrifices need to be \Nacceptable to Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.98,0:30:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,as was Jesus’.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.12,0:30:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What made Jesus so pleasing? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.86,0:30:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he did everything \Nthe way Jehovah wanted him to do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.76,0:30:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, he said something \Nthat we want to say one day: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.16,0:30:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“I always do the things pleasing to him.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.03,0:30:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And one day in perfection, \Nwe will be able to say that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.97,0:30:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus was pleasing \Nin his word, in his deed, in his actions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.41,0:30:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how can we imitate Jesus \Nand thus imitate Jehovah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.54,0:30:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s briefly discuss three ways. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.31,0:30:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,First: Pray for God’s holy spirit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.52,0:30:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,When confronted with trials, \Nwhat did Jesus do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.62,0:30:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He did not rely on himself; \Nhe petitioned Jehovah for help. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.69,0:30:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we’re struggling with a temptation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.26,0:30:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,—a certain fleshly weakness—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.36,0:30:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s vital that we do the same. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.03,0:30:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We can also talk to the elders\N—our loving shepherds—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.67,0:30:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,who will pray with us,\Nand they will definitely help us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.47,0:30:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to remain faithful \Nwith words of encouragement.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.97,0:31:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Number two: Obey Jehovah completely. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.14,0:31:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus always did things \Nthat were pleasing to his Father. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.58,0:31:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Luke 22:42 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.92,0:31:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“Let, not my will, but yours take place.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.55,0:31:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, \Nthere is no substitute for obedience. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.89,0:31:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We cannot be acceptable without obedience. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.19,0:31:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Number three: Know the Scriptures well. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.66,0:31:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus used God’s Word as his authority. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.73,0:31:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,His whole life revolved around knowing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.70,0:31:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and obeying and encouraging others \Nabout God’s laws. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.51,0:31:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We all have busy schedules. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.51,0:31:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We have work to do \N—busy in the congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.31,0:31:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s more than just trying to find time \Nto dig deep into God’s Word; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.12,0:31:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,we must make the time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.65,0:31:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what do our schedules tell us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.45,0:31:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,about our love for Jehovah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.09,0:31:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,our love for his Word? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.63,0:31:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we read the Bible daily? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.03,0:31:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we do, \Nhow much time do we take \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.73,0:32:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to let it sink into our mind \Nand our heart and to meditate? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.24,0:32:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we content with just looking \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.24,0:32:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,at the basics\N—the surface—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.24,0:32:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,or digging deeper and deeper \Nbelow the surface?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.71,0:32:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s vital that we train \Nour minds and our hearts, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.88,0:32:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but it takes time \Nand it takes effort, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.68,0:32:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,just as a marathon runner \Nmust devote much time and effort \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.02,0:32:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to his training to run a race. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.99,0:32:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, as we know, \NChristians are likened \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.36,0:32:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to running a race, \Nand it’s a race for life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.56,0:32:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s see \Nwhat the apostle Paul had to tell us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.56,0:32:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If we go over to 1 Corinthians, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.67,0:32:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,1 Corinthians chapter 9, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.07,0:32:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,a scripture we know very well, \Nand we’ll start in verse 24. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.74,0:32:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are a few key elements \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.34,0:32:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that we would like to extract \Nas we’re reading these verses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.98,0:32:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Here Paul said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.75,0:32:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do you not know \Nthat the runners in a race all run, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.45,0:32:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“but only one receives the prize? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.12,0:32:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“Run in such a way that you may win it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.86,0:32:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“Now everyone competing in a contest \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.43,0:33:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“exercises self-control in all things \N[there’s a key]. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.23,0:33:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“Of course, they do it \Nto receive a crown that can perish, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.40,0:33:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“but we, one that does not perish. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.80,0:33:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“Therefore, the way \NI am running is not aimlessly; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.44,0:33:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“the way I am aiming my blows \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.47,0:33:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“is so as not to be striking the air; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.78,0:33:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“but I pummel my body \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.91,0:33:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“[and the footnote says, \N“punish; strictly discipline”] \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.52,0:33:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,“and lead it as a slave, \Nso that after I have preached to others, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.39,0:33:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“I myself should not become disapproved \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.76,0:33:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,[or the footnote says, “disqualified”] \Nsomehow.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.70,0:33:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So we definitely want to have \Nself-control like a runner. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.37,0:33:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to say no to Satan’s world \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.50,0:33:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and yes to things \Nthat are acceptable to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.84,0:33:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And we definitely want \Nto make sure that we are acceptable \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.48,0:33:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and never to be disapproved. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.11,0:33:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps we can illustrate this. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.18,0:33:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,In the 1994 New York City Marathon, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.35,0:33:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,there was a young man named German Silva, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.19,0:34:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and he ran an outstanding race. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.92,0:34:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, there was only half a mile \Nto the finish line in Central Park, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.09,0:34:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and somehow he got distracted. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.13,0:34:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He took the wrong path. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.13,0:34:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he lose the race? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.77,0:34:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the lead runner took over. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.97,0:34:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he got redirected; \Nhe went back on the path; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.27,0:34:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,he began to run faster and faster. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.87,0:34:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He passed up the lead runner, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.88,0:34:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and he won the New York City Marathon \Nby two seconds. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.58,0:34:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What does this tell us? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.58,0:34:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It tells us that sometimes \Nwe can lose our focus, we can be sidetracked, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.59,0:34:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,or we could get involved \Nin unacceptable conduct. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.62,0:34:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But allow God’s Word \Nand loving shepherds to readjust our course. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.16,0:34:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Never give up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.16,0:34:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a few years later, after that\N—1997—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.93,0:34:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,German began running again \Nin a New York City Marathon. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.20,0:34:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He thought he had this one all in the bag; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.30,0:34:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,he thought he was going to win this race. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.31,0:34:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But he started to run slower. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.41,0:34:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He began to— \NHe dehydrated. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.94,0:35:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of taking \Njust a few seconds to hydrate, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.05,0:35:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,he skipped that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.55,0:35:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He thought he could do it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.88,0:35:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what could this tell us? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.89,0:35:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we cannot afford to take shortcuts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.19,0:35:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to have \Na regular intake of spiritual food \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.46,0:35:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep pace with Jehovah’s organization. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.93,0:35:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We do this \Nby what the commenters told us today, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.93,0:35:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that is, a regular intake \Nof God’s Word and meditation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.60,0:35:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,As we run the Christian course\N—the race for life—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.60,0:35:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,remember, it’s not the speed, \Nit’s the direction\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.94,0:35:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,—that’s what matters the most. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.01,0:35:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And may we always run in such a way \Nthat is acceptable to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.05,0:35:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,As Brother Curzan mentioned, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.68,0:35:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,certainly a regular intake of God’s Word \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.49,0:35:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,can have a dramatic effect on our lives. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.32,0:35:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Take the example of Rafika Morris. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.63,0:35:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Her life led her on a search \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.90,0:35:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,for ways to achieve racial harmony \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.33,0:35:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,through human means. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.44,0:36:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But after years of frustration \Nand disappointments, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.21,0:36:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,how would studying the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.71,0:36:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,affect her search for answers? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.75,0:36:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Growing up in the South \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.75,0:36:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,during the time of segregation\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.16,0:36:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,—blacks and whites—\Nwe couldn’t mix. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.59,0:36:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And not only that, they had signs \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.43,0:36:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep you knowing \Nwhere you were supposed to go. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.60,0:36:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t understand \Nwhy we couldn’t get along.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.50,0:36:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Fifty cents.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.50,0:36:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Sir. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.44,0:36:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Sir.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.54,0:36:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandma, he’s just a boy. \NWhy are you saying “Sir”?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.91,0:36:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Be quiet. \NI want you to know your place.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.55,0:36:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I told her after we got back on the truck: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.58,0:36:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,“You know what? \NI’ll never hold my head down!”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.39,0:36:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,My grandmother \Nknew I had a love for the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.56,0:36:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because I would \Nalways read the Bible as a kid. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.06,0:36:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But I couldn’t understand it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.04,0:37:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to pray, \N“What makes us so different?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.07,0:37:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, \N“Why can’t we live together?”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.61,0:37:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I met a group, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.25,0:37:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and this group was like \Nwhat I really wanted to be in. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.22,0:37:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They were about politics. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.72,0:37:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They said, “We’re fighting injustice.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.93,0:37:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And when they said \Nthat word “injustice,” it was like, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.99,0:37:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Yeah, this is what I want to be in, right?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.60,0:37:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,‘To be part of something that can change \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.90,0:37:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and make people united, right?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.34,0:37:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That was my goal.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.57,0:37:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We started protesting about police brutality, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.34,0:37:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and I think that’s what a lot of people, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.91,0:37:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, \Nwere focusing on. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.42,0:37:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I liked some of the things \Nthat they were doing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.25,0:37:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but they trained us every, \Nevery day in military training. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.52,0:37:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We learned how to use weapons \Nand stuff like that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.02,0:37:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I’m thinking: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.39,0:38:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,‘This is not what I want to be in. \NThis is not what I joined.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.66,0:38:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So I started going back to God again\N—to reading the Bible—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.83,0:38:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was like \NI’m not changing anything. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.54,0:38:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible that I was reading \Nwas the King James Version. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.61,0:38:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was reading it, reading it, reading it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.77,0:38:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but I couldn’t understand it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.01,0:38:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We went to Jamaica, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.01,0:38:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and we saw this Bible, \Nthe New World Translation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.88,0:38:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And I started reading it, \Nand it made so much sense! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.55,0:38:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And I could understand it, \Nand it wasn’t “thee” and “thou.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.52,0:38:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I was like, ‘Wow!’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.69,0:38:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, like, \N‘This is the one I want to get.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.06,0:38:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, two women knocked on the door. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.76,0:38:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t know they were Jehovah’s Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.70,0:38:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All I could see was that Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.07,0:38:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, \N“Where did you get that Bible from?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.14,0:38:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And they said, \N“OK, we’ll bring you one.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.41,0:38:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And they did. \NSo they brought me the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.37,0:38:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but I didn’t know I was going to have \Na Bible study that came along with it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.21,0:38:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The first time I went \Nto a convention of Jehovah’s Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.72,0:38:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it was like ten thousand people. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.32,0:38:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,When I went in there and I saw \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.75,0:39:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,all these different faces \Nand different colors, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.22,0:39:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it was like Jehovah showing me: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.03,0:39:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“Hey, Rafika, remember you were asking me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.33,0:39:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“about all different people \Ngetting together and being one? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.40,0:39:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,See, I’m not partial; \Nthey do get along; we are unified.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.40,0:39:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And it just made me feel so good inside. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.64,0:39:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.34,0:39:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the organization \Nthat I want to be in.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.84,0:39:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I just see people as people, you know, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.05,0:39:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and I can preach \Nand be friends with anybody. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.95,0:39:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that I know \Nwhat the Bible really teaches, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.56,0:39:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a wonderful life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.29,0:39:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because I know \Nthat only God and his government \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.00,0:39:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,can bring about peace.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.80,0:39:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like how Jehovah \Nunified everybody, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.97,0:39:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I want everybody \Nto be unified\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.57,0:39:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and come to know Jehovah, \Njust like I know him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.11,0:39:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah answered my prayer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.02,0:40:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,While Rafika faced unique challenges \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.02,0:40:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,early in her spiritual life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.19,0:40:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,she learned to trust in Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.86,0:40:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust is also needed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.30,0:40:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,if we choose to extend ourselves \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.73,0:40:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in a new form of Kingdom service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.90,0:40:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This is especially true \Nof those who have had the privilege \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.24,0:40:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to attend the School \Nfor Kingdom Evangelizers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.51,0:40:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Their personal experiences confirm this. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.15,0:40:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I have an illness \Nthat affects my level of energy, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.99,0:40:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so I didn’t feel that I could accept \Njust any kind of assignment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.26,0:40:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the end of this system is near, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.73,0:40:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to do whatever I can \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.73,0:40:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah wants down to the very end. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.73,0:40:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So I applied. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.94,0:40:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Before attending SKE, \Nwhen I received my invitation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.74,0:41:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,all of a sudden I had challenges \Nor worries about myself. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.74,0:41:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt unworthy, even unqualified.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.01,0:41:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Being a single sister, \Ngoing into the class with so many couples, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.02,0:41:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I would be out of place. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.09,0:41:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I used all my abilities. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.10,0:41:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like my head was swelling up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.27,0:41:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, I felt \Nthat I was really being refined \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.87,0:41:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and ended each day feeling fulfilled.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.81,0:41:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Something that I \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.31,0:41:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,really enjoyed about SKE \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.91,0:41:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,was Friday afternoons. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.58,0:41:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s when we had a talk \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.58,0:41:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,from one of the Governing Body members. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.32,0:41:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That was special.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.72,0:41:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,During the eight weeks of school, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.72,0:41:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,such an emphasis was placed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.16,0:41:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,on serving where the need is greater. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.16,0:41:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So this way of thinking \Nbecame more important to us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.16,0:41:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,After eight weeks of attending the school, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.16,0:41:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you are even ready to be sent to the moon.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.80,0:42:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was told \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.13,0:42:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that my next assignment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.60,0:42:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,would be in Mesa, Arizona, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.84,0:42:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, ‘Where is that?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.84,0:42:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I thought, \N‘Oh, no, scorpions!’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.48,0:42:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I thought, ‘OK, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.81,0:42:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,this is where Jehovah thinks \NI should be, so I’m ready to go.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.65,0:42:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the challenges in my new assignment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.65,0:42:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,was finding suitable accommodations. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.32,0:42:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a couple in the congregation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.42,0:42:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,who had two rooms that they rented \Nin the back of their property,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.16,0:42:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but it needed some renovations. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.16,0:42:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So the brothers very quickly came together, \Nhelped sort it out, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.26,0:42:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and even built an extra \Nlittle kitchenette lounge. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.27,0:42:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So now we have a beautiful little home \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.27,0:42:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to go back to after a long, \Nhot day in the ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.14,0:42:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I always thought that I’d do much better \Nin the cold than I would in the heat. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.14,0:42:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So the brothers and sisters \Nwere very helpful \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.01,0:42:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,in making sure that I stayed hydrated, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.22,0:42:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,making sure I knew \Nhow to handle myself in the heat, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.55,0:42:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,giving me pointers on things to carry, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.39,0:42:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and they made sure that I had \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.56,0:43:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,an extra-large water bottle with me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.46,0:43:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We really felt supported by the congregation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.43,0:43:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,because they found us an apartment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.73,0:43:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This meant that we could concentrate \Non our ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.57,0:43:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the things that really helped me \Nwas an experienced brother \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.34,0:43:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,who gave an encouraging comment \Nabout whether my health \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.81,0:43:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,would permit me to attend the school. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.85,0:43:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, “If she can pioneer, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.35,0:43:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,then it’s also possible for her \Nto attend the school.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.16,0:43:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The education that we received at SKE \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.73,0:43:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,especially helped us with our qualities, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.16,0:43:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,our personality \N—putting on the new personality. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.90,0:43:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That really will help us \Nnot only now in our assignment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.24,0:43:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but right through into the new world. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.24,0:43:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I think there are many \Nwho could meet the qualifications \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.78,0:43:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,with just a little more effort. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.25,0:43:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Please know that there is \Na wonderful education program, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.72,0:43:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and we were able \Nto experience it in our 60’s. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.22,0:44:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We could get through it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.69,0:44:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So if others are thinking of applying, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.56,0:44:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to tell them \Nthat we were able to do it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.06,0:44:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and by all means, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.13,0:44:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I want them to taste \Nthe same joy that we experienced. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.07,0:44:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You could be nervous \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.57,0:44:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and have performance anxiety \Nand worry about, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.88,0:44:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,‘How will I handle answering, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.94,0:44:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,‘and how about all \Nof the student assignments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.28,0:44:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and the tests?’\N—worries like that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.65,0:44:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But for my own part, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.65,0:44:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it was two months \Nwith an incredible amount of joy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.66,0:44:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have to focus on that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.22,0:44:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a gift \N—it is a wonderful gift from Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.50,0:44:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn’t sure if I was going \Nto put in the application \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.57,0:44:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because I thought maybe \NI wanted to do it as a couple \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.30,0:44:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than as a single person. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.67,0:44:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But I prayed to Jehovah about it, \Nand I put my application in. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.51,0:44:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn’t be experiencing the happiness \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.84,0:44:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that I have now if I had waited. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.98,0:45:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So I’m happy \Nthat I just put my application in \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.58,0:45:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and let Jehovah do the rest. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.58,0:45:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, sometimes I’m driving \Ndown the freeway, and I think: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.85,0:45:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Wow, Jehovah, I am so happy! \NThank you!’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.92,0:45:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,These experiences remind me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.59,0:45:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of Colossians 3:23, 24 which reads: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.90,0:45:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“Whatever you are doing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.90,0:45:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“work at it whole-souled as for Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.84,0:45:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“and not for men, \Nfor you know that it is from Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.31,0:45:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“you will receive \Nthe inheritance as a reward. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.31,0:45:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Slave for the Master, Christ.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.42,0:45:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly, these brothers \Nand sisters are doing just that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.95,0:45:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If you personally find yourself in a position \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.12,0:45:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to reach out for a privilege, \Nsuch as attending this school \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.16,0:45:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,or moving to where the need is great, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.06,0:45:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,give it consideration. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.00,0:45:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we travel to Costa Rica, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.87,0:46:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,where we find our brothers \Nand sisters relying on Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.07,0:46:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,as they prepare for a very special assembly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.65,0:46:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why was trust in Jehovah \Nessential for this project? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.80,0:46:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we asked the branch for permission. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.07,0:46:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Once they gave us approval, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.84,0:46:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,we began to make preparations \Nfor the assembly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.31,0:46:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,though we had absolutely nothing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.25,0:46:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So one brother lent us a property \Nfor the assembly site. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.72,0:46:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brothers have brought \Nmany different skills to the project. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.15,0:46:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There are metalworkers ,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.16,0:46:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,cabinetmakers, and bricklayers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.92,0:46:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Many brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.16,0:46:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,have given of their resources \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.69,0:46:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and used their abilities \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.30,0:46:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so that this project could go ahead. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.37,0:47:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This has really made us stand out here. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.80,0:47:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,People were asking each other: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.14,0:47:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“What is happening here?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.24,0:47:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and “Who paid for all of this?”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.81,0:47:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They say people are surprised \Nat how many workers are coming to help. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.81,0:47:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And I wonder, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.71,0:47:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,‘If this is getting attention now, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.65,0:47:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,what will the assembly be like?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.39,0:47:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,A comfortable, practical, \Nand secure Assembly Hall \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.39,0:47:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,was constructed using materials \Nacquired locally. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.43,0:47:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Expectations grew \Nas the special day drew closer, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.03,0:47:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and when it finally arrived, \Nthose in attendance \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.17,0:47:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,experienced something truly moving. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.81,0:47:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,With Jehovah’s help, \Nmany interested ones, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.91,0:47:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,along with our brothers and sisters, \Nhave come here today \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.21,0:47:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to celebrate our first assembly \Nin the Bribri language. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.82,0:47:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Friends, this is wonderful! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.93,0:48:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When the program started in Bribri, I cried.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.46,0:48:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m so happy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.17,0:48:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to have participated in the assembly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.74,0:48:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,especially because it’s in my own language. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.27,0:48:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s what we wanted. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.08,0:48:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We hope it continues just like this.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.78,0:48:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We walked a long way to invite these people, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.59,0:48:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and to see them here, \Nit makes me very happy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.83,0:48:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The information presented \Nin the local language \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.76,0:48:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,touched many hearts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.60,0:48:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This was truly a historic event \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.87,0:48:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,for our indigenous brothers in Costa Rica. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.97,0:48:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has made it possible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.97,0:48:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for more people in this isolated region \Nto enjoy his spiritual blessing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.82,0:49:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you note why trust in Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.06,0:49:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,was so essential for this project? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.33,0:49:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,At the start the brothers had nothing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.10,0:49:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But they trusted \Nthat Jehovah would assist them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.14,0:49:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and he did through donated land, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.11,0:49:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,materials, and willing volunteers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.54,0:49:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we can truly put \Nour confidence in Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.68,0:49:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,as he guides us \Nthrough this system of things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.48,0:49:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Such trust in Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.19,0:49:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is highlighted \Nin this month’s music video entitled \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.09,0:49:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Confident in You. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.83,0:49:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a tree planted in the ground, \NYour words have sunk deep down \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.68,0:50:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Into my heart and soothed my mind \Nwith gentle thoughts of peace. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.79,0:50:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,’Cause no matter what may come, \NWith this wisdom from above, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.27,0:50:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I always have these truths \Nto keep reminding me to \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.28,0:50:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Go on; don’t be afraid. \NHold on to what Jehovah says. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.29,0:50:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Through all the storms, your words have \NGiven me strength to endure. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.43,0:51:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And every day I am more \Nconfident in you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.18,0:51:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,When this world tries to pull me down, \NTo give up on what I’ve found, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.36,0:51:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I turn to you and know that you \Nare always there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.13,0:51:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes time to meditate— \NGet the words from off the page \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.61,0:51:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And in my heart so they can help \Nand guide me to \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.52,0:51:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Go on; don’t be afraid. \NHold on to what Jehovah says. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.50,0:52:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Look beyond any adversity. \NFocus on the things that I can’t see.  \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.14,0:52:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Through all the storms, your words have \NGiven me strength to endure. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.28,0:52:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And every day I am more \Nconfident in you— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.13,0:52:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.51,0:52:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Go on; don’t be afraid. \NHold on to what Jehovah says. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.09,0:53:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Look beyond any adversity. \NFocus on the things that I can’t see. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.37,0:53:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Through all the storms, your words have \NGiven me strength to endure. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.04,0:53:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And every day I am more \Nconfident in you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.52,0:53:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This month we have seen \Nhow trusting in Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.09,0:53:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and his guidance \Ncan assist us in a variety of ways: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.50,0:53:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,addressing issues with a close friend, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.17,0:53:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,our choices in entertainment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.74,0:53:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and even coping with a world \Nfilled with social injustice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.07,0:53:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly, Jehovah \Nis someone in whom we can trust! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.25,0:53:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But we have one last treat \Nfor you before we end our program. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.08,0:54:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll briefly travel to Cádiz, Spain. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.69,0:54:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Cádiz is considered to be one \Nof the oldest cities in Western Europe \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.06,0:54:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and was founded by the Phoenicians. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.36,0:54:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It is situated on a narrow slice \Nof land surrounded by the sea. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.73,0:54:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Cádiz has a wealth of vistas \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.97,0:54:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and well-preserved historical landmarks. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.24,0:54:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,On the outskirts \Nlies Puerto de Santa María, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.38,0:54:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,where an English-speaking \Ncongregation meets. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.45,0:54:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This congregation is made up mainly \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.22,0:54:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of brothers and sisters \Nserving as need-greaters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.55,0:54:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They have come from other parts \Nof Spain as well as distant lands, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.90,0:54:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,such as Australia, Britain, \NCanada, and the United States. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.93,0:54:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Cádiz has a high rate of unemployment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.04,0:54:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,so finding work is not easy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.07,0:54:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,One couple travels nearly 300 miles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.54,0:54:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,(or 483 km) \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.47,0:54:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,every Thursday to their territory, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.21,0:55:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and on Monday morning they make \Nthe trip back to where they live and work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.75,0:55:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In spite of these financial challenges, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.42,0:55:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,many are still serving \Nas construction volunteers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.52,0:55:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,remote Bethel workers, and pioneers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.57,0:55:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brothers and sisters \Nin Puerto de Santa María \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.91,0:55:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,are thrilled to send their love \Nand greetings to you all. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.88,0:55:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This is JW Broadcasting \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.65,0:55:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,from the world headquarters \Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses. \N
